cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS

The paper proposes a neural network-based model for fraud early detection, which involves handling user activity sequences and predicting survival probabilities. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Among these, cs.LG is the most likely category as the paper heavily relies on recurrent neural networks for modeling user activities. The paper also deals with security-related issues, which makes cs.CR a likely category as well. The use of survival analysis and the focus on predicting probabilities suggest that cs.AI and cs.SI could also be relevant categories. Finally, the use of machine learning techniques and the focus on handling sequential data suggest that cs.DS could be a relevant category as well.
